"Caldeira K., Duffy P.B.","The role of the southern ocean in uptake and storage of anthropogenic carbon dioxide",2000,"Science","287","5453",,"620","622",,,10.1126/science.287.5453.620,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0034723386&partnerID=40&md5=88be3a4db79eb347d402c87931cb9055","Climate System Modeling Group, Lawrence Livermore Natl. Laboratory, Livermore, CA 94550, United States","Caldeira, K., Climate System Modeling Group, Lawrence Livermore Natl. Laboratory, Livermore, CA 94550, United States; Duffy, P.B., Climate System Modeling Group, Lawrence Livermore Natl. Laboratory, Livermore, CA 94550, United States","An ocean-climate model that shows high fluxes of anthropogenic carbon dioxide into the Southern Ocean, but very low storage of anthropogenic carbon there, agrees with observation-based estimates of ocean storage of anthropogenic carbon dioxide. This low simulated storage indicates a subordinate role for deep convection in the present-day Southern Ocean. The primary mechanism transporting anthropogenic carbon out of the Southern Ocean is isopycnal transport. These results imply that if global climate change reduces the density of surface waters in the Southern Ocean, isopycnal surfaces that now outcrop may become isolated from the atmosphere, tending to diminish Southern Ocean carbon uptake.",,"carbon dioxide; surface water; air-sea interaction; anthropogenic source; carbon cycle; carbon dioxide; article; density; dispersion; global climate; model; priority journal; sea; Southern Ocean",,"carbon dioxide, 124-38-9, 58561-67-4",,,,"Sarmiento, J.L., Sundquist, E.T., (1992) Nature, 356, p. 589; Keeling, C.D., Piper, S.C., Heimann, M., (1989) Aspects of Climate Variability in the Pacific and Western American, 55, pp. 305-363. , Geophysical Monograph Series, D. H. Peterson, Ed. American Geophysical Union, Washington, DC; Tans, P.P., Fung, I.Y., Takahashi, T., (1990) Science, 247, p. 1431; Sabine, C.L., (1999) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 13, p. 179; Maier-Reimer, E., Hasselmann, K., (1987) Clim. Dyn., 2, p. 63; Siegenthaler, U., Sarmiento, J.L., (1993) Nature, 365, p. 119; Sarmiento, J.L., Orr, J.C., Siegenthaler, U., (1992) J. Geophys. Res., 97, p. 3621; Sarmiento, J.L., Le Quere, C., Pacala, S.W., (1995) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 9, p. 121; Sarmiento, J.L., Hughes, T.M.C., Stouffer, R.J., Manabe, S., (1998) Nature, 393, p. 245; Gruber, N., Sarmiento, J.L., Stocker, T.S., (1996) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 10, p. 809; Gruber, N., (1998) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 12, p. 165; Poisson, A., Chen, C.-T., (1987) Deep Sea Res. Part A, 34, p. 1255; Murphy, P.P., Freely, R.A., Gammon, R.H., Kelly, K.C., Waterman, L.S., (1991) Mar. Chem., 35, p. 77; Duffy, P.B., Caldeira, K., (1997) Geophys. Res. Lett., 24, p. 1323; Caldeira, K., Duffy, P.B., (1998) Geophys. Res. Lett., 25, p. 1003; Pacanowski, R., Dixon, K., Rosati, A., (1991) The G.F.D.L Modular Ocean Model Users Guide Version 1.0, Gfdl Ocean Group Technical Report 2, 2. , NOAA/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, Princeton, NJ; Oberhuber, J.M., (1993) J. Phys. Oceanogr., 23, p. 808; Duffy, P.B., Eby, M., Weaver, A.J., (1999) Geophys. Res. Lett., 26, p. 1739; Martinson, D.G., (1990) J. Geophys. Res., 95, p. 11641; Joos, F., Plattner, G.-K., Stocker, T.F., Marchal, O., Schmittner, A., (1999) Science, 284, p. 464; Matear, R.J., Hirst, A.C., (1999) Tellus Ser. B, 51, p. 722; Wanninkhof, R., (1992) J. Geophys. Res., 97, p. 7373; Levitus, S., Boyer, T.P., Temperature (1994) World Ocean Atlas 1994, NOAA Atlas NCSDIS, 4. , vol. 4 National Oceanographic Data Center, Silver Spring, MD; Bryan, K., (1984) J. Phys. Oceanogr., 14, p. 666; Orsi, A.H., Johnson, C.C., Bullister, J.L., (1999) Prog. Oceanogr., 43, p. 55; Broecker, W.S., Sutherland, S., Peng, T.-H., (1999) Science, 286, p. 1132; Watson, A.J., (1999) Nature, 401, p. 902; note","Caldeira, K.; Climate System Modeling Group, Lawrence Livermore Natl. Laboratory, Livermore, CA 94550, United States; email: kenc@llnl.gov